Module kivakit.interfaces
Package com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.comparison

Interface Matcher<Value>

Type Parameters:
Value - The type of value to match
All Superinterfaces:
Matchable<Value>, Predicate<Value>
All Known Subinterfaces:
Filter<Value>, MessageFilter, Password
All Known Implementing Classes:
AllMessages, DigestPassword, MessagesOfType, MessagesWithSeverityOf, PlainTextPassword, ResourceGlob
Functional Interface:
This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
@FunctionalInterface public interface Matcher<Value> extends Matchable<Value>, Predicate<Value>
A matcher implements Predicate, but adds some KivaKit-specific functionality.

Interface Methods

  • boolean matches(Value value) - Functional interface that matches against a single value, returning true if it matches and false if it does not
  • matcher() - Default method that implements Matchable so that all Matchers are Matchable

Factories

  • matchAll() - Matches all values
  • matchNothing() - Matches nothing
  • matching(Pattern) - Matches the given regular expression Pattern
  • matching(Predicate) - Matches the given Predicate
  • matchObjectNamed(String) - Matches any Named object with the given name
